You love his craft even if you don't agree with any or all of his viewpoints on life and everything within it.He's probably the best song-writer of any time.So stop dithering and just buy the damn thing like I did.

reviewText: I started getting into Morrissey about 8 years ago when my sister started listening to The Smiths just out of high school. I've been lucky to see Morrissey in concert four times now (three out of the four were in the front row, all three in the front with a handshake. I want to capitalize handshake btw.) Watching this really did make me feel like I was seeing him live again.Now onto this bluray. It is top notch as far as concert blurays that I've seen. The picture quality is 9/10. It is impossible to not notice the difference between a bluray and a dvd when you watch this with a decent tv and an entry level 5.1 system (or a good stereo system.) I did sing out loud for a few of my favorites. That might sound cliche... but I did have a few vodka shots in me and it was pretty loud. My system consists of a Yamaha 5.1 entry level receiver that delivers more than enough power to my Def Tech speakers. My living room gets pretty loud and the sound was better than I imagined. I'm picky when it comes to sound (mostly internet connected high def stuff like youtube or netflix) but this bluray really had a great soundstage and great lossless sound. The only problem I had with the 5.1 mix is I didn't really hear my rear channels much, other than symbols.The picture quality is great. It's a 1080p transfer and most concert blu's only get a 1080i transfer. Which I guess is essentially a 720p transfer. All I know is this video transfer is the best concert bluray I've seen... Moz fan or not.They also don't change camera angles every 0.5 seconds which is nice.***Bottom line is if you are a Morrissey fan you'll probably buy the bluray or dvd. I'd spend the little extra and get the bluray if you have the player.***Also, check out meetyourmeatdotcom and learn why Morrissey, my sister, cousin and I are Vegetarians.I owe you one, Moz :)
summary: Moz knows how to put on a show
